### Code Splitting + Tree Shaking

Tree shaking removes unused exports during build time, while code splitting separates code into chunks for lazy loading. Together they minimize main bundle and load features on-demand. Webpack requires ES6 modules and production mode.

```typescript
// webpack.config.js
module.exports = {
  mode: 'production',
  optimization: {
    usedExports: true,
    splitChunks: { chunks: 'all' }
  }
};

// Dynamic import for splitting
const module = await import('./heavy-feature');
// Unused exports in heavy-feature are tree-shaken
```

**Common interview trap:** Forgetting that tree shaking only works with ES6 modules and production mode.

answer.ru:
