// Неиспользуемые экспорты удаляются
```

**Типичная ошибка:** Забыть, что tree shaking работает только с ES6 модулями и в режиме production.

answer.en:
### LCP vs INP

LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) measures loading performance—when the largest visual element appears. INP (Interaction to Next Paint) measures responsiveness—how long the page takes to respond to user interactions. Optimize LCP first for initial load perception, then focus on INP if interactions feel sluggish.

```typescript
// Monitor both metrics
const observer = new PerformanceObserver((list) => {
  for (const entry of list.getEntries()) {
    if (entry.name === 'largest-contentful-paint') {
      console.log('LCP:', entry.startTime);
    }
  }
});
observer.observe({ entryTypes: ['largest-contentful-paint', 'interaction'] });
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing LCP with FCP (First Contentful Paint)—LCP specifically targets the largest element.

answer.ru:
